# Shutters — Project Core

Vanilla JS + CSS accordion library. **No framework, no runtime deps.** Node ≥ 14, Vite 6 dev-only, ES2020 target.

## Source of truth

- JS class: `src/shutters-core.js`
- Library entry: `index.js` (imports CSS for Vite; re-exports class)
- CSS mechanics: `src/shutters-core.css`
- CSS theme: `src/shutters-theme.css`
- Marketing site: sibling **shutters-site** repo (`file:../shutters` npm dependency — no synced copies)

## Hard constraints

- **Vanilla JS forever** — plain `.js` source, zero runtime npm deps, DOM APIs only (see `vanilla-js-only.mdc`)
- Never add runtime npm dependencies
- Never `import './shutters-core.css'` inside `shutters-core.js`
- Never set `window.ShuttersAccordion` in ES module code (UMD build handles globals)
- Event delegation only: one click + one keydown listener per container
- Animate with CSS Grid `grid-template-rows: 0fr/1fr` — not max-height or scrollHeight JS
- JS auto-applies ARIA (`role="button"`, `tabindex="0"`, `aria-expanded`, `aria-controls` + panel `id`)
- Keep `:focus-visible` visible — never `outline: none` without replacement

## After structural changes

```bash
npm run agent:sync
npm run build
```

